cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.CV. 

The paper proposes a new RL problem that requires the agent to generalize to a previously-unseen environment characterized by a subtask graph. The paper also proposes a neural subtask graph solver (NSGS) to solve this problem. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the following sub-categories: 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) because the paper proposes a new RL problem and a neural network-based solution. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) because the paper proposes a new learning problem and a neural network-based solution. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) because the paper proposes a new RL problem that can be applied to robotics. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) because the paper proposes a new RL problem that involves control and decision-making. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) because the paper presents experimental results on two 2D visual domains.
